{
  "id": "helix-board-integration",
  "title": "Full Automaker board integration with Helix project — connect to Automaker server",
  "category": "automation",
  "description": "Connect the Helix project to the running Automaker server so the board, auto-mode, and agent execution work correctly. This requires Automaker MCP server connectivity.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Automaker server running (`npm run dev` in the protoMaker directory)\n- Automaker MCP plugin installed and connected to Claude Code\n- Valid `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in environment\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Open the Automaker board at `http://localhost:3007`\n2. Add the Helix project path (`/Volumes/Development/helix`) to the project list\n3. Verify the features created in `.automaker/features/` appear on the board\n4. Verify `.automaker/settings.json` is loaded correctly\n5. Test by starting an agent on `helix-agent-roles` (the safest first feature)\n6. Confirm agent can read context files and project structure\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Helix project appears in Automaker board\n- All 14 alignment features are visible\n- Agent can execute in a worktree without errors\n- Context files are loaded into agent prompts",
